    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <details>
        <summary>What determines your zodiac sign?</summary>
        <p>Your zodiac sign, also called your sun sign, is determined by the position of the Sun on the date you were born. The zodiac is divided into 12 segments of roughly 30 degrees each, and the Sun passes through one segment per month as the Earth orbits it. The sign the Sun occupied at the moment of your birth is your zodiac sign. For example, if you were born on April 5, the Sun was in Aries, making you an Aries. You can <a href="/astrology-calculators/zodiac-sign-calculator/">find your exact zodiac sign here</a>.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What are the zodiac elements?</summary>
        <p>The 12 zodiac signs are divided into four elements, each containing three signs. Fire signs (Aries, Leo, Sagittarius) are passionate and energetic. Earth signs (Taurus, Virgo, Capricorn) are practical and grounded. Air signs (Gemini, Libra, Aquarius) are intellectual and communicative. Water signs (Cancer, Scorpio, Pisces) are emotional and intuitive. Your sign's element shapes your fundamental approach to life, relationships, and challenges.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Can your zodiac sign change?</summary>
        <p>No, your zodiac sign does not change. It is determined by your date of birth and remains the same for your entire life. Some people born on the boundary between two signs, known as a cusp, may feel influenced by both signs, but the Sun was in one specific sign at the moment of your birth, and that is your true sun sign. Claims that zodiac signs have shifted due to a "new" 13th sign (Ophiuchus) apply to the sidereal zodiac used in some Eastern traditions, not the tropical zodiac used in Western astrology.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What's the difference between sun, moon, and rising signs?</summary>
        <p>Your sun sign represents your core identity, ego, and the energy that drives your personality. Your moon sign reflects your emotional inner world, subconscious needs, and how you process feelings. Your rising sign, also called your ascendant, is the sign that was on the eastern horizon at the exact time and place of your birth, and it governs first impressions and how others perceive you. Together, these three placements form the "big three" of your astrological profile and provide a much more complete picture than your sun sign alone.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Which zodiac signs are most compatible?</summary>
        <p>Signs that share the same element tend to be highly compatible. Fire signs (Aries, Leo, Sagittarius) pair well together, as do Earth signs (Taurus, Virgo, Capricorn), Air signs (Gemini, Libra, Aquarius), and Water signs (Cancer, Scorpio, Pisces). Complementary elements also work well: Fire and Air signs energize each other, while Earth and Water signs ground and nurture each other. For a detailed analysis of any two signs, try our <a href="/astrology-calculators/zodiac-compatibility-calculator/">zodiac compatibility calculator</a>.</p>
      </details>
    </section>

